<div type="dyad" n="3">
<p><supplied reason="subaudible"><quote type="basetext" xml:lang="san-Latn">
<lg met="anuṣṭubh">
	<l>pratyahaṁ deśadr̥ṣṭaiś ca śāstradr̥ṣṭaiś ca hetubhiḥ |</l>
	<l>aṣṭādaśasu mārgeṣu nibaddhāni pr̥thak pr̥thak ||</l>
	</lg>
	<note type="parallels">
        <list>
          <item><bibl><ptr target="MDhŚ08.003"/></bibl></item>
        </list>
  </note>
</quote></supplied></p>
<p>*sari<!-- the unreduplicated form is not recorded in OJED --> masiha sirān ṅiṅət-iṅəta <app><lem type="norm">makasādhanaṅ</lem><rdg wit="#L">makasa:danaṁ</rdg><rdg wit="#K">makasḍanaṁ</rdg></app> vara-varah saṅ hyaṅ āgama <app><lem wit="#K">mānavādi</lem><rdg wit="#L">manava:vī</rdg></app>,
mvaṅ sakinapagəhaknikaṅ sapañjiṅ deśanya, <app><lem wit="#K">deśa ṅaranya,</lem><rdg wit="#L"/></app>
sadaṅayan<supplied reason="omitted">,</supplied> sajamus vuṅkal, savuravan, sakanuruhan,
an hana *kaparǝkanya deniṅ āgama, ya hika deśadr̥ṣṭa ṅaranya,
<!-- AG+TL have reached here on 2020-05-06 -->
<app><lem type="conj" rend="check">aṅkǝn</lem><rdg wit="#L #K">hankan</rdg></app><!-- maybe anǝka[kǝ]n> 'to cause to come (to), cause to reach, give, send, communicate'
