<div type="dyad" n="4">
<p><supplied reason="subaudible"><quote type="basetext" xml:lang="san-Latn">
	<lg met="anuṣṭubh">
	<l>hiṁsāṁ yaḥ kurute kaś cid deyaṁ vā na prayacchati |</l>
	<l>sthāne te dve vivādasya <app><lem source="#svayambhu"><!-- @AG+TL: the lemma from this stanza in the Svayambhu itself supports the reading bhinne as opposed to bhinno -->bhinne</lem><rdg source="#Mandlik1886_01">bhinno</rdg><note>Mandlik's reading is also supported by a manuscript collated in Olivelle 2005.</note></app> ’ṣṭādaśadhā punaḥ ||</l>
	</lg><note type="parallels">
         <list>
          <item>This stanza is absent from <bibl><ptr target="bibl:Olivelle2005_01"/>Olivelle</bibl>'s constituted text, though it is referenced in his app. crit. for one manuscript. The stanza occurs in ed. <bibl><ptr target="bibl:Mandlik1886_01"/>Mandlik<!-- <citedRange unit="chapter">8</citedRange><citedRange unit="stanza">4</citedRange>--></bibl> 8.4 shows <foreign>bhinno</foreign>, but the Svayambhu implies <foreign>bhinne</foreign>.</item>
          <!-- alternative suggestion for computer-actionable bit simpler referencing of editions bib:Mandlik1886_01_ed08.0004 -->
        </list>
	</note>
  </quote>
</supplied></p>
<p><term xml:lang="san-Latn"><app><lem type="emn">hiṁsāṁ yaḥ</lem><rdg wit="#L">Iṅsīya</rdg><rdg wit="#K">Iṅsa:ya</rdg></app> kurute kaś cit</term>,
hana vvaṅ mamātyani nirdoṣa, <app><lem wit="#K">maṅlarani nirdoṣa,</lem><rdg wit="#L"/></app>
kunaṅ <term xml:lang="san-Latn">deyam <app><lem type="norm">vā</lem><rdg wit="#L #K">va</rdg></app> na <app><lem type="emn">prayacchati</lem><rdg wit="#L #K">prayaścati</rdg></app></term>,
tan paveh irikaṅ yogya <app><lem wit="#L">vehakna</lem><rdg wit="#K">vehikna</rdg></app>, aveh irikaṅ tan yogya vehaknanya kunaṅ,
<term xml:lang="san-Latn"><app><lem wit="#L">sthāne</lem><rdg wit="#K">svane</rdg></app> te dve vivādasya</term>,
ya <app><lem wit="#L">ikā</lem><rdg wit="#K">hikaṁ</rdg></app> sthānaniṅ vyavahāra, rvaṅ siki <app><lem wit="#K">mūlanya</lem><rdg wit="#L">malanya</rdg></app>,
<term xml:lang="san-Latn"><app><lem type="norm">bhinne</lem><rdg wit="#L #K">bhine</rdg></app> <app><lem type="emn">’ṣṭādaśadhā</lem><rdg wit="#L">ṣṭedaśada:</rdg><rdg wit="#K">ṣṭedaśada</rdg></app> punaḥ</term>,
matmahan ta ya vvalu vlas vkasan.</p>
</div>
