<p>lvirnya: <term xml:lang="san-Latn"><app><lem>teṣām ādyam r̥ṇādānam</lem><rdg wit="#L">tapīm adyam r̥ṣada:nī</rdg><rdg wit="#K">tepaṃ<unclear>m a</unclear>dyam r̥sadanaṃ</rdg></app></term>,
tan <app><lem type="conj">kasahuraniṅ hutaṅ</lem><rdg wit="#L">kasahurapihutaṁ</rdg><rdg wit="#K">kasahurapyutaṁ</rdg><note>Our conjecture is inspired by a passage in the Tantri Kāmandaka, p. 30: <foreign>maṅkana kagavayaniṅ yajñadharma, mvaṅ kasahuraniṅ utaṅ</foreign>.</note></app>, hādiniṅ vyavahāra.
